findings.title: Denial of service attacks
findings.description: General Vulnerability include some common vulnerabilities that may appear in smart contract projects. These vulnerabilities are mainly related to the characteristics of the smart contract itself, such as integer overflow/underflow and denial of service attacks.

findings.title: Flash loan attack caused by incorrect setting of price acquisition oracle
findings.description: The flash loan attack vulnerability arises from the incorrect configuration of the price acquisition oracle.

findings.title: Stake losses due to integrated third-party protocol
findings.description: The project may suffer stake losses due to the integrated third-party protocol.
